Rinse and trim green beans. Add beans to boiling water. Cook, uncovered, on medium-high heat 7-8 minutes. Drain. (For frozen green beans, cook following package directions. Drain.) Melt butter in a small saucepan; stir in wine, vanilla, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Simmer 2 minutes. Toss butter sauce with green beans. Top with toasted almonds.